The Duchess of Sussex, Meghan Markle, has met with a group of women leaders in Cape Town, to better understand the roles they play in their communities. They included former anti-apartheid activists, academics and politicians such as Sophia de Bruyn, Mamphela Ramphele and Professor Mamokgethi Phakeng. They shared their struggles for gender equality and womenâ€™s empowerment. The Duchess says she has been fighting for the rights of women and girls most of her life, and that it has been very powerful to hear first-hand from all of them. She says gender-based violence is a global issue.   